&lt;li&gt;Masters in Public Policy, International Relations or Law.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;The successful candidate’s starting salary will be determined based on a number of non-discriminating factors, including qualifications for the role, level, skills, experience, location, and balancing internal equity relative to peers at DV.&lt;br&gt;The estimated salary range for this role based on the qualifications set forth in the job description is between [$109,000 - $178,000]. This role will also be eligible for bonus/commission (as applicable), equity, and benefits.&lt;br&gt;The range above is for the expectations as laid out in the job description; however, we are often open to a wide variety of profiles, and r

&lt;h3&gt;About DoubleVerify&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DoubleVerify is a pioneering market leader known for its cutting-edge technology that impeccably authenticates the quality of digital media, thus optimizing ad performance for globally renowned brands. DoubleVerify (DV) offers media transparency and accountability to deliver the highest level of impression quality, ensuring maximum advertising performance. Since its inception in 2008, DV has been instrumental in helping hundreds of Fortune 500 companies optimize their media investments and in forging a more robust advertising industry. To learn more about us, please visit &lt;a href=&quot;http://doubleverify.com&quot;&gt;doubleverify.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Scibids AI&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Scibids AI is DoubleVerify&#39;s performance optimization solution that uses artificial intelligence to enhance advertising campaigns. The technology integrates with major demand-side and social media platforms to optimize campaigns in real-time, using client-defined KPIs. Scibids operates with the best interest of the advertiser and is agnostically available on every major buying platform.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic &lt;strong&gt;Product Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to lead Scibids’ efforts to make Authentic Advantage, our new strategic product, a success on all major social media platforms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Authentic Advantage is an ambitious offering that combines our industry-leading brand suitability (Prebid) and performance optimization technologies (Scibids) into a single, cohesive solution designed to achieve superior outcomes in digital ad buying.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Product Manager in our New York office, you will define release roadmaps for each platform, setting clear conditions for success. You will collaborate closely with Engineering, Sales, and Operations to define the go-to-market strategy, to build features that drive product adoption and reduce operational load, and to strategically position the bundled value proposition of brand suitability and performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have a deep understanding of the ad tech ecosystem, particularly the intricacies of social media advertising, brand safety, and performance marketing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Vision: &lt;/strong&gt;Own the roadmap for Scibids bundling into Authentic Advantage and feature enhancements, aligning product strategy with business goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Development: &lt;/strong&gt;Manage development from concept ideation to product release, including requirement gathering and breaking down the vision to epics and stories.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Intelligence&lt;/strong&gt;: Understand the competitive marketplace to influence strategy, identify gaps where the Authentic Advantage team can innovate and drive the changes needed to implement them by pivoting quickly when needed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partnership Liaison&lt;/strong&gt;: Act as a product liaison for Business Development on Authentic Advantage to adjust trade-off between quality and performance depending on clients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;: Collaborate across the entire DV organization by working with DV&#39;s broader Social product teams on joint ventures product marketing to structure go-to-market releases and create compelling narratives around new Authentic Advantage integrations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work experience:&lt;/strong&gt; A minimum of 3 years of product management experience, with ideally 1-2 year

